This paper is about pre-training deep neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG). The specific application domain is speech recognition, which suggests that the paper could also be classified under natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper proposes a new pre-training approach that is based on knowledge transfer learning, which is a technique commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The approach is applied to recurrent neural networks (RNNs), which are a type of neural network commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.NE). Finally, the paper presents experimental results on a speech recognition task, which suggests that it could also be classified under computer vision (cs.CV) since speech recognition involves processing audio signals.
